---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Zirpo and the photographs." />
</head>
<body class="bg-surface text-on-surface min-h-screen flex flex-col">
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-grow pt-32 pb-24 px-8 md:px-16 max-w-[800px] mx-auto w-full">
    <!-- Quote as header -->
    <header class="mb-24 md:mb-32 text-center">
      <blockquote class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-headline italic font-light max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-tight text-on-surface">
        "To know a thing well, know its limits. Only when pushed beyond its tolerances will true nature be seen."
      </blockquote>
      <cite class="block mt-6 font-label text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-outline not-italic">Frank Herbert</cite>
    </header>

    <!-- About text -->
    <article class="font-body text-base md:text-lg text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed space-y-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p>
        I'm Zirpo. I don't really know why I photograph. I'm not an artist. But something about this form of expression caught me off guard in my late thirties — an age when most people have long settled their hobbies.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm drawn to both sides: the image and the machine. The technical process fascinates me as much as the result. That's why I also shoot analog — including developing black and white at home. There's a rhythm to it that digital doesn't have.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most of the time I use a Fujifilm X-T4 with a manual lens. I shoot RAW and JPG, but my focus is on getting it right in camera — straight out of camera, using Fuji's film simulations. Black and white for street and casual work. Porta 400 for events. Sometimes I build custom simulations with AI, tailored to a specific place or moment. Those more personal shots may not end up here often.
      </p>

      <p>
        This page exists for a simple reason: to make me go out and shoot more.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
